First, we need to find the symmetric difference between A and B (A △ B). The symmetric difference between two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection.

A = {2, 4, 6, 8}
B = {3, 4, 7}

Intersection of A and B: {4}
A △ B = {2, 3, 6, 8, 7}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between (A △ B) and {4, 7, 9}.

(A △ B) = {2, 3, 6, 8, 7}
{4, 7, 9}

Intersection of (A △ B) and {4, 7, 9}: {7}
(A △ B) △ {4, 7, 9} = {2, 3, 6, 8, 4, 9}

So, the symmetric difference (A △ B) △ {4, 7, 9} is {2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9}.
